{
  "texts": [
    "This analysis enables the automatic injection of all relevant dependency signatures and import statements into the prompt, thereby significantly increasing the likelihood of generating compilable code.",
    "Advancing this approach, ASTER [108] statically identifies types requiring mocking and pre-fills the prompt with a test skeleton that already includes necessary mocking framework setups (e.g., Mockito).",
    "The impact of such preanalysis is substantial, directly reducing the primary cause of compilation failures.",
    "As documented in multiple studies, \"symbol not found\" errors constitute a major obstacle, accounting for up to 43.6% of all compilation failures [161,167].",
    "By proactively providing dependency information, these static analysis techniques fundamentally address this prevalent failure mode."
  ]
}